# AI DROPSHIPPING AGENT — PROJECT RULES
# Cursor reads this file automatically. Never ignore it.

## WHAT WE ARE BUILDING
An autonomous dropshipping marketing agent that:
1. Discovers trending products (via Minea scraper using Rod/headless Chrome)
2. Evaluates margins and supplier data (via Sup Dropshipping API)
3. Reasons about which products to test (via OpenAI gpt-4o)
4. Launches and monitors ad campaigns (via Meta Ads API, TikTok Ads API)
5. Learns from every outcome and stores lessons (SQLite memory layer)
6. Communicates with the owner via WebSocket + Vue dashboard

## STACK
- Backend: Go 1.22+, Chi router, gorilla/websocket, go-rod (scraper), go-sqlite3
- AI: OpenAI API (gpt-4o) via github.com/sashabaranov/go-openai
- Frontend: Vue 3 + Vite (in /frontend directory)
- Database: SQLite at ./data/agent.db
- Config: environment variables loaded from .env

## EXISTING RESOURCES (owner already has these)
- Minea Basic account (email/password login, no public API — we scrape via Rod)
- Two Shopify stores: one for tech accessories, one for pet products
- OpenAI API key (gpt-4o)
- Cursor Pro
- Meta Business account (API app review pending — stubs used until approved)

## TDD RULES — NON-NEGOTIABLE
1. Write the test file FIRST. The test must fail before implementation begins.
2. Every exported function and method must have at least one test.
3. Use table-driven tests for all logic with multiple cases.
4. Use interfaces for all external dependencies so they can be mocked in tests.
5. Run `go test ./...` after every implementation step. All tests must pass before moving on.
6. Integration tests (hitting real network) go in files tagged `//go:build integration`
7. No "we'll add tests later". If you find yourself writing that, stop and write the test first.

## PROJECT STRUCTURE
cmd/
  agent/main.go          — entrypoint
  scrape-minea/main.go   — one-shot scraper CLI for debugging
  smoke-test/main.go     — DEV_MODE integration smoke (health, API, WS, chat)
internal/
  agent/
    agent.go             — main agent loop (phases: discover, reason, approve, launch, monitor, learn)
    knowledge.go         — AgentKnowledgeCore constant (dropshipping expertise baked in)
    memory.go            — learning/memory layer
    decision.go          — product scoring + campaign decision engine
  integrations/
    openai/client.go     — gpt-4o reasoning client
    minea/scraper.go     — Rod-based headless scraper
    sup/client.go        — Sup Dropshipping API
    meta/client.go       — Meta Ads API
    tiktok/client.go     — TikTok Ads API
  api/
    server.go            — HTTP + WebSocket server
    handlers.go
  store/
    db.go                — SQLite setup and migrations
    models.go            — all data structs
config/
  config.go
frontend/               — Vue 3 + Vite app (router, useApi, useWebSocket, views, components)

## KEY BUSINESS RULES (the agent must know these)
- Winning product price range: €15–€80 (impulse buy zone)
- Minimum viable gross margin: 30% (below this = structurally unprofitable with paid ads)
- BEROAS formula: 100 / GrossMargin%. Example: 30% margin → BEROAS = 3.33
- Scale threshold: actual ROAS must be ≥ BEROAS × 1.25 before scaling budget
- Kill threshold: pause if spend > 50% of per-unit gross profit with zero purchases
- Kill threshold: pause if CPA > (selling price - COGS) after 3 days
- TikTok role: DISCOVERY (top-funnel, cheap CPMs €2.60-6.60, UGC-style creative)
- Meta role: CONVERSION (closing + retargeting, median ROAS 2.2x, Advantage+ campaigns)
- Creative refresh: every 2-3 weeks on TikTok, monthly on Meta
- Product saturation signal: trending heavily for >6 weeks = likely past peak

## OWNER NOTIFICATION RULES
- Severity levels (lowest to highest): "info" | "warning" | "critical"
- NOTIFY_MIN_SEVERITY controls which events trigger out-of-band delivery
- Default min severity is "critical" — only critical events leave the dashboard
- Critical events that ALWAYS notify out-of-band regardless of dashboard state:
    * Credit balance below minimum safe threshold (< 100 credits)
    * Credit quota exhausted for current session
    * Auth token expired and re-login failed
    * No communication channels configured (log warning once on startup)
    * Campaign auto-killed with spend > €50
    * Agent cycle failed 3 consecutive times
- Warning events (notify if NOTIFY_MIN_SEVERITY=warning or lower):
    * Credit balance below alert threshold (< 200 credits)
    * Campaign CPA trending toward kill threshold
    * Approval request pending > 12 hours
- Info events (notify if NOTIFY_MIN_SEVERITY=info):
    * Daily performance summary
    * New product approved for testing
    * Lesson learned and saved
- If NO notification channels are configured in .env:
    * Log a warning on startup: "No notification channels configured —
      critical alerts will only appear in the dashboard"
    * Send a dashboard Message of type "alert" as fallback
    * Never panic or fail — degraded mode is acceptable

